review_blob: Aroma of lighter citrus and slightly floral. Gold color, white head and slight haze. Flavor is of toasted malt and resiny citrus. Some lemon. Sweetness at beginning. Bitterness is firm and lingers without astringency. Fuller body than expected with moderately high carbonation.

Bottle from Trader Joes. Light color for amber ale. Aroma is malty/bready with some toast highlights. No hops or esters. Alcohol is quite evident for a 7.1%abv beer. Flavor is lightly toasty with no hop flavor. Finish is dry from alcohol. Cleanly fermented. Medium body and carbonation. Alcohol is far to dominating as a flavor characteristic. Bittering just keeps it from being sweet.
